html:
369 U.S. 427

82 S.Ct. 879

8 L.Ed.2d 7

G. W. WARREN
v.
J. Edwin LARSON, as State Treasurer, etc.

No. 920, Misc.

Supreme Court of the United States

April 16, 1962

Rehearing Denied June 11, 1962.

See 370 U.S. 920, 82 S.Ct. 1559.

Walter Warren, for appellant.

Richard W. Ervin, Atty. Gen. of Florida, and Robert J. Kelly and Gerald Mager, Asst. Attys. Gen., for appellee.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.

2

Mr. Justice BLACK and Mr. Justice DOUGLAS are of the opinion that probable jurisdiction should be noted.

3

Mr Justice FRANKFURTER and Mr. Justice WHITE took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
